desc_content.paragraph: Developer module: this module is dedicated only for developers. It allows implements and configures remotedev in cleep

desc_signature.desc_annotation:
= 'Developer module helps you to develop on Cleep installing and preconfiguring sync tools. It also provides a full page that helps you to check and build your own application.
This module will provide the official way to publish your module on Cleep market.

Lot of resources are available on developer module wiki, have a look and start enjoying Cleep!'

desc_content.paragraph: Build application archive (zip format) Archive is not protected by password

field_body.paragraph: True if application archive generated successfully

definition.paragraph: url (string): archive url, name (string): archive name (usually name of module)

desc_content.paragraph: Select application for development. It save in config the module, and enable debug. It also disables debug on previous module in debug if any.

field_body.paragraph: module_name (string) – module to enable development on
